{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2692a3a7-dc0b-4cc7-aef1-d89c4541e19f","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n**1. In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n- **Remove** the assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n- **Add** the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (which includes the framework, adapter, and test SDK)\n\nReplace your `<ItemGroup>` sections with:\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**2. In `OrderServiceTests.cs`:** No changes needed — the `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace and attributes (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`) are the same in MSTest v3.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n| Remove | Add |\n|--------|-----|\n| `<Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />` | `<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />` |\n| `<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />` | *(included in MSTest package)* |\n\nThe `MSTest` v3 meta-package bundles `MSTest.TestFramework`, `MSTest.TestAdapter`, and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`, so you only need the one reference.\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad6f2b64-475e-4c1e-b7eb-c23ced8551fb","outputTokens":363,"requestId":"BC21:2657C1:20B47C5:2481263:69FAA68C"},"id":"33b4cbd3-92c4-4ac3-bcfd-f9e9f4bc15a4","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:25:23.856Z","parentId":"31432426-9468-4bc0-89c1-65df26e62477"}
